HEADWORD: Ripeness
<hw>Ripe"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>r⟦imac⟧pness</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state or quality of being ripe;
maturity;; completeness; perfection; <as>as, the <ex>ripeness</ex> of
grain; <ex>ripeness</ex> of manhood; <ex>ripeness</ex> of
judgment.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Time, which made them their fame outlive,⟦br⟧
To Cowley scarce did <qex>ripeness</qex> give.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

